snippet.textDisplay:
Hi 👋 Shane I’m happy you’re posting a bit more again you and your friends are amazing ❤️

I’m depressed and I found your main channel in 2018 and started to watch you and your squad.
The way you and your friends made (make) me laugh was unbelievable and very liberating.

Back then - I thought/
“1) Laughing was the opposite of being depressed.
2)If I could laugh this much I really thought I was in the making of saying goodbye to my depression” (That momentum didn’t happen though).

A couple of months ago I saw a TEDx talk and I learned a very valuable thing about depression and that was:
“The opposite of being depressed isn’t laughing and for a second feeling ok.
👉The opposite of depression is VITALITY”

It was at this moment I fully understood why I still was and felt depressed.

When your spirit entered my life around 2 years ago, you and your beautiful group of friends have impacted as well as improved my life so much and that is something I will forever be grateful for, appreciate and cherish.

When I watch your videos, you and your friends reaches me in a way I didn’t know was possible,
Shane, you and your squad makes me feel like myself for a while and that’s an amazing, beautiful and a bit in a positive way overwhelming feeling ❤️
I mean when people I don’t know and when I feel I’m at my lowest, can impact me in the most beautiful way possible and making me feel happy and laugh and just forget everything for a minute that’s everything 🙏❤️
Thanks dear Shane and your beautiful amazing friends and family
Love ❤️
/ Grace
